result.adr_address: 29-31 Gough St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: YakiniKuu Japanese Bbq

reviews.text: The lady who served us was very friendly and nice. Food was good.
Really enjoyable!  Great concept and very tasty food.

The air con was freeezing, for ladies make sure you bring along a jacket. I ordered a regular wagyu set lunch and was told it would be more lean than the deluxe set but the fact was the otherwise. It was much fatter than the deluxe set. The price was high given there were only 10 small pieces of meat given. Service was horrendous and the waitress just came by often to so called clear up your desk when there were merely two plates and bowls. One waitress even came to switch off our stove without getting our permission! It was such a disturbing lunch! Won’t come for sure given the price and the service.
Nice lunch within 200hkd

Visited Yakinikuu for dinner yesterday with a group of 8. Total check was for HKD ~5,000 Service was horrendous and waitress was shameless about how bad the service was. We had to ask 3-4 times every time we needed our tea refilled - waitress would then tell us their service is good - thick skin. Price is very expensive for very small portions. When we got the bill/check, the waitress added multiple extra orders of meat that we did not order or receive - when we brought it to her attention, she did not even apologize... suggest people go elsewhere - there are better yakiniku choices for better value and service
